ional Ornithologists' Union (IOC). Alternate names include the \"black-faced flycatcher\", \"carinated flycatcher\", \"grey-winged monarch\" (particularly in New Guinea to distinguish from black-winged monarch), \"grey-winged monarch flycatcher\" and \"pearly-winged monarch\". The species is monotypic: no subspecies are recognised. Within the genus, it is most closely related to the black-winged monarch (Monarcha frater). Description The black-faced monarch is grey, with rufous underparts and mature birds have a black patch on the face. Distribution and habitat The preferred habitat is rainforest and wet forest. References External links Xeno-canto: audio recordings of the black-faced monarch", "shortSummary": "The black-faced monarch (Monarcha melanopsis) is a passerine songbird in the family Monarchidae found along the eastern seaboard of Austral…", "locations": ["路易·皮埃尔·维埃约", "William Swainson", "Gregory Mathews"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Monarcha_melanopsis_1_-_Brunkerville.jpg/960px-Monarcha_melanopsis_1_-_Brunkerville.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-monarcha", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-monarcha-melanopsis", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-monarcha", "species": "taxonomy-species-monarcha-melanopsis"}, "expandable": true, "x": -180.6, "y": -228.87, "z": 244.79}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-monarcha-melanopsis", "name": "Black-faced monarch", "latinName": "Monarcha melanopsis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Black-faced monarch（Monarcha melanopsis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Black-faced monarch。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -180.6, "y": -228.87, "z": 252.05}], "links": [{"key": "bird-black-faced-monarch-5a06fbf2__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-sp